y would operate. These\nresults point out that no social distancing should be relaxed before mid August\n2020. If relaxations are necessary, they should not be performed before the\nbeginning this date and should be in small periods, no longer than 25 days.\nThis paradigm would proceed roughly until January/2021. The second peak of\ninfections, which has a forecast to the beginning of October, can be reduced if\nthe periods of no-isolation days are shortened.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 May 2020 17:24:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-22"}
